{"id":14881393,"mediaExerciseId":"00549af8-508b-4257-87c7-51f6697b20cb","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"13","chapterTitle":"Return, Risk, and The Security Market Line","groupId":612375,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":451,"solutions":[{"id":5992411,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We are asked to determine if the provided statement is correct or incorrect in this exercise.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/18770019f5be72d474032ef539e3da6f/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/18770019f5be72d474032ef539e3da6f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **variance** of investment's return quantifies how each amount in the series of investments deviates from average and consequently from another value in the group.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/bd4de74471baf474456b220f29305d86/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/bd4de74471baf474456b220f29305d86/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"A well-diversified portfolio's volatility is solely a factor of systematic risk. This portfolio variance may measure how evenly spread apart investments' results are concerning their average. The higher the variance, the higher the unpredictability. This also affects the risk level of the set of values. The variation of individual assets assists in estimating the overall risk measure.\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/f8a70887ec31a45675feeea6ec7f9ea7/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/f8a70887ec31a45675feeea6ec7f9ea7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**The variance is not an important factor in evaluating a well-diversified portfolio's expected return. As a result, the statement is incorrect.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/9b8902f9408884092f1cff909c468438/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/c65ba636aee0268ffbd07db0258300c7/9b8902f9408884092f1cff909c468438/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"ebe9091e-2f3d-4c8c-947e-bf75672c4aa1","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881394,"exerciseName":"7","page":451,"